data.name: label10.Text
data.value:
This app listens to UDP packets coming in on the 'Listen Port' . It can then re-send (reflect) these packets to a new destination IP and port (Reflect IP and Reflect Port). The source IP of the reflected packets must be one of the IP addresses assigned to a NIC on the local machine. The options are listed in the Reflect Src IP combo box
Do not run in steady state with 'Long Term Debug' on. App will eventually hang.
The debug window will clear after every 100 packets are received.
ToDo: May not show all IPv4 addresses for NICs that have more than One IPv4 address assigned. -Add iterator to check for multiple IPv4 addresses on single adapter Main loop has two lines that update Text Boxes. This should be moved to a separate thread for performance.
